It is a buffet style restaurant which has take out only for for now do to COVID 19 virus. Required that you wear mask for entry or no service. There is a hand pump sanitizer at the front of counter to use before you begin serving yourself. Sweet Mama's has several food items to choose from such as oxtail, collard greens, mac & cheese, ziti, fish, cabbage, jerk chicken, bbq chicken, yams. There is also fresh fruits, cakes and canned beverages. The food is good but can be pricey which is about $5.99 a pound and is weighed on a scale. It is a good place to go for a quick bite to eat but not everyday unless you can afford to spend between $10.00-$20.00 plus tax. Credit & debit cards are accepted.

Sweet Mama's has great food no question, in fact, I did a large catering order with them very recently. My issue is with the employees and management. You service a community that services your business and maybe we forget how much economic power we really have. There were two (2) incidents that I encountered. The first was after I placed a large order (40+ people),  I had discrepancies with pricing. The price on the on-line catering menu is different from when you actually go in to place the order. Different amounts online vs. in store is unprofessional advertising.  I even increased my order the week before to have a different invoice written with an even higher amount. After everything was said and done, there were no amenities. Not that they were obligated to, but sometimes for inconvenience sake, it just good business and again an order of 40+ people.  The other incident was a defamatory comment made whereby the behind the counter employee accepted a $50.00 bill from a patron and then another patron paid with a $20.00 which the employee proceeded to examine against the light to determine whether it was counterfeit. When questioned by the patron paying with the $20.00 the manager’s response was “white people ALWAYS have money” as to infer the community that frequents you does not? I can only assume that this will be the same establishment that will price gouge in the event of an emergency. Regardless of how good the food is, is it worth being served by people who think we are less than themselves but good enough to spend our money? In these times of blatant discrimination, I felt it necessary to inform other consumers so you can CHOOSE where to spend OUR money, wisely and perhaps elsewhere!
